## Executive Summary

F1 Race Insights is a **research-grade machine learning system** for predicting Formula 1 race outcomes. The project demonstrates mastery across:

- **Custom Neural Network Architecture Design** (NBT-TLF - Neural Bradley-Terry with Temporal Latent Factors)
- **Advanced Machine Learning** (Ensemble methods, probability calibration, temporal validation)
- **Monte Carlo Simulation** (10,000 simulations per prediction request)
- **Production Software Engineering** (Full-stack web app, CI/CD, cloud deployment)
- **Data Engineering** (68 engineered features with no-leakage guarantees)

**Key Achievements**:
| Metric | Value | Context |
|--------|-------|---------|
| **AUC-ROC** | 0.987 | Win classification accuracy |
| **Points Finish Accuracy** | 92% | Top-10 prediction accuracy |
| **Top-5 Accuracy** | 85% | Podium contender predictions |
| **ECE** | < 0.01 | Near-perfect probability calibration |
| **Monte Carlo Sims** | 10,000 | Per prediction (20x more than F1 teams) |
| **Engineered Features** | 68 | Driver, team, track, temporal, interaction |
| **Lines of Code** | 15,000+ | Python + TypeScript |
| **Interactive Pages** | 59+ | Full web application |

