## 14. Key Talking Points for Applications

### Research & Innovation
> "I designed a custom neural network architecture called NBT-TLF that combines the classical Bradley-Terry pairwise comparison framework with learned entity embeddings and sinusoidal positional encoding from Transformer architectures. This hybrid approach captures both the mathematical guarantees of ranking theory and the representational power of deep learning."

### Engineering Excellence
> "The system implements strict temporal validation to prevent data leakage—a critical but often overlooked aspect of time-series ML. Every feature is computed using only historically available data, and the walk-forward backtesting framework ensures fair evaluation."

### Full-Stack Capability
> "I built the entire system end-to-end: from data ingestion using the FastF1 API, through feature engineering and model training, to a production-deployed web application with 59+ interactive pages, a RESTful API, and automated CI/CD deployment to AWS."

### Statistical Rigor
> "The system achieves 0.987 AUC with near-perfect probability calibration (ECE < 0.01), validated through walk-forward backtesting on 97 races. I implemented isotonic regression for probability calibration to ensure the predicted probabilities are reliable for decision-making."

